<Page xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      Title="The File Menu">
    <FlowDocumentReader ViewingMode="Scroll">
        <FlowDocument>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"
                       FontSize="16pt">
                The File Menu
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>File</Bold> menu lets you load and save ink.
                The program does not retain the file name of the ink file
                you've loaded, or warn you that you haven't yet saved
                the ink on the canvas.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>New</Bold> menu item clears the canvas. If you
                haven't saved the ink, it is lost.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Open</Bold> menu item lets you load a file in
                the Ink Serialized Format (ISF).
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Save</Bold> menu item lets you save a file in
                the Ink Serialized Format.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                In addition, the <Bold>Save</Bold> menu item lets you save
                a XAML format file containing a <Italic>Drawing</Italic>
                object representing the ink outlines and colors. You can
                use this XAML file when programming graphics under the
                Windows Presentation Foundation. See Chapter 22 of the
                book
                <Hyperlink NavigateUri="http://www.charlespetzold.com/wpf">
                    Applications + Code + Markup
                </Hyperlink>
                for details.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Exit</Bold> item terminates the program.
            </Paragraph>
        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentReader>
</Page>
